# Bilingual Content Rules

## Pattern

- **One language at a time** via header toggle (not stacked, not side-by-side).
- Default language: **Urdu** (`ur`).
- Persistence: `localStorage['ber-lang']`.
- Use `useLanguage()` from `apps/web/src/i18n/useLanguage.ts`.

## Content shape

```ts
const copy = {
  title: { ur: 'بستانِ رحمت', en: 'Bustan-e-Rahmat' },
} as const;
const { lang, t } = useLanguage();
t(copy.title); // returns string for active lang
```

## Direction & fonts

- When `lang === 'ur'`: `dir="rtl"`, Urdu font families, `line-height: var(--leading-urdu)`.
- When `lang === 'en'`: `dir="ltr"`, English font families.
- `LanguageProvider` sets `document.documentElement.lang` and `.dir` — do not fight it.
- Never mix fonts across languages on the same element.

## Quran / Arabic

```tsx
<span lang="ar" className="quran">...</span>
```

- Centered, Indopak Nastaleeq font (`var(--font-arabic)`), `var(--color-teal-700)`.

## Toggle UI

- Reuse `LanguageToggle` from `apps/web/src/i18n/LanguageToggle.tsx` in header/nav.
